## 3) Palette — 22 merchant colors on `:root`

The storefront injects variables on **`:root`**. **Always** use `var(--variable-name, #fallback)` so the UI stays usable if a value is missing or empty.

| CSS variable | Purpose |
|--------------|---------|
| `--hd-bg`, `--hd-text` | Header background & text |
| `--ann-bg`, `--ann-text` | Announcement bar |
| `--ft-bg`, `--ft-text` | Footer |
| `--buy-btn-bg`, `--buy-btn-text`, `--buy-btn-border` | Buy / add-to-cart |
| `--crt-btn-bg`, `--crt-btn-text`, `--crt-btn-border` | Cart button |
| `--product-name-text`, `--product-price-text`, `--product-sale-price-text` | Product typography |
| `--body-bg`, `--body-text` | Page base |
| `--input-border`, `--input-bg`, `--input-text` | Inputs (normal + focus); checkout inputs often use `.checkout-form .global_input` in examples |
| `--checkout-form-bg`, `--checkout-heading-text` | Checkout shell & headings |

**Practice:** Prefer **palette variables** for colors merchants should control from the dashboard. Use **`theme_data`** for settings beyond those 22 colors (copy, toggles, repeatable lists, layout options).

**Prestig repo note:** `style.css` may define additional **`--ps-*`** design tokens. When styling surfaces tied to merchant-facing palette (buttons, header, footer, checkout), **wire through palette vars** (or values derived from them) so admin color changes still apply.

