## 6) Link interception (SPA)

- Same-origin links like `/products/...`, `/collections/...`, `/search`, etc. use **client-side navigation** in sections where interception is enabled — docs list **header, footer, categories, products, slider, breadcrumbs** among typical cases.
- **Not** intercepted: external domains, `target="_blank"`, links with `download`.
- Use normal `<a href="...">` for internal routes; no extra attributes required.

---

## 7) Custom events — golden rules

1. Use **`new CustomEvent('event-name', { bubbles: true, detail: {...} })`**.
2. **`bubbles: true` is required** — the app listens on the section container (`useLiquidEvents`), not only the clicked node.
3. Dispatch from **inline `onclick`** or **`script.js`** on an element inside the section.

### Complete event table (official)

| Event | Section / context | `detail` | Behavior |
|-------|-------------------|----------|----------|
| `cart-click` | Header | — | Opens side cart drawer |
| `lang-click` | Header | `{ anchor: HTMLElement }` **recommended** | Language UI — pass the opening control as `detail.anchor` |
| `register-click` | Header | — | Client-side `/register` when `is_register_active`; use `register-btn` |
| `footer-subscribe` | Footer | `{ email: string }` | Newsletter — **trimmed** email |
| `review-open` | Reviews | — | Opens review modal |
| `buy-now` | Fixed buy | — | Buy / add flow |
| `increment-quantity` | Fixed buy | — | +1 |
| `decrement-quantity` | Fixed buy | — | -1 |
| `quick-add` | Product listings | `{ productId: string }` | Quick add to cart |
| `quick-view` | Product listings | `{ productId: string }` | Quick view modal |
| `toggle-wishlist` | Products / PDP | `{ productId: string }` | Wishlist toggle |
| `toggle-compare` | Products / PDP | `{ productId: string }` | Compare + modal |
| `compare-click` | Header | — | Opens compare modal |
| `go-home` | Thanks | — | Home navigation |
| `copy-tracking-link` | Order invoice | `{ link: string }` | Copy tracking URL + toast |

On product cards, use `event.preventDefault(); event.stopPropagation();` before `dispatchEvent` for add / wishlist / compare buttons.

**Event flow (docs):** Liquid / `script.js` → `CustomEvent` bubbles → React section wrapper → `useLiquidEvents` → app logic.

